From James Callison Subject Re Do trains busses have radar In article Rick 'Open VMS ' Colombo writes I don't know about trains but I've saw a sign on the back of a Greyhound bus that warns you that your radar detector may be set It doesn't explain why but it does set off my radar Because Greyhound has apparently gotten around to installing their RADAR collision prevention They use RADAR to monitor how close other vehicles are and how fast their relative speeds are and signals a warning to the driver if they're coming up on something too fast or are getting too This is all I remember from the news reports a few months back at the time they were only talking about the possibility of installing the They didn't mention how it worked in bumper to bumper traffic or how it discriminated between a Camaro approaching at and ye olde bridge support in the median being approached at on a I do recall something about progressive stages of warnings from flashing lights to audible warnings ie it goes from a red Too close light to hysterically screaming WE'RE ALL GOING TO DIE James James Callison Microcomputer Coordinator U of Oklahoma Law Center C C DISCLAIMER I'm not an engineer but I play one at The forecast calls for ' T Bird SC It's a hell of a thing killing a You take away all he has and all he's ever gonna Will Munny Unforgiven